STATE OF OKLAHOMA DISPOSITION
FLOOR AMENDMENT No. ________
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
(Date)
I move to amend Senate Bill No. 555 as follows:
On page 1, line 23, by inserting after “A.” and before the word “There” the following: “1.”;
On page 2, line 8 ½ by inserting a new paragraph 2 as follows:
“2. A school district seeking an exemption pursuant to this subsection shall not be granted an
exemption to the following:
a. the Teacher Due Process Act of 1990,
b. the criminal history record check requirements of Section 5-142 of Title 70 of
the Oklahoma Statutes,
c. the employment contract requirements of Section 6-190 of Title 70 of the
Oklahoma Statutes,
d. state laws relating to the education of children with disabilities,
e. the Oklahoma School Testing Program Act and the accountability system
provided for in Section 1210.545 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
f. the minimum salary schedule,
g. financial reporting and auditing requirements, and
h. participation in the Teachers’ Retirement System of Oklahoma and health
insurance programs.”;
And, by amending the title to conform.
